code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='coerce')
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['actual', 'normal'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data['actual'], data['normal']], labels=['Actual', 'Normal'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of actual temperature compared to normal temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['forecast'])
    plt.plot(data['forecast'], data['actual'], color='blue', label='Actual')
    plt.plot(data['forecast'], data['normal'], color='green', label='Normal')
    plt.plot(data['forecast'], data['record'], color='red', label='Record')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of forecasted temperature over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['record'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.hist(data['record'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['record'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['record'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of recorded temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['record'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['record'], data['forecast'], color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Recorded Temperature')
    ax.set_ylabel('Forecasted Temperature')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between recorded temperature and forecasted temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
